commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, there is a match command that associates the contact to a
job based on their respective ID.

However, there is no way to un match a contact from the job.

Creating a UnmatchCommand class enables the user to un match a
candidate from their job.

List of files added:
- UnmatchCommand.java - the main logic in un matching the contact and
the job
- UnmatchCommandParser.java - the parser which process user input
before sending it to UnmatchCommand.java

files edited:
- AddressBookParser.java - Added UnmatchCommandParser.java so it is
visible to the addressbook

The GUI does not show highlights for skills and requirements.

Fix the styling issue to have better UI experience.

Update DarkTheme.css to include skills and requirements.

Currently, the two variables jobName and contactName in the
MatchCommand class are used to represent the identifiers of
jobs and contacts. However, these names can be misleading,
as they suggest the variables represent the actual names of the job
and contact, rather than their unique identifiers.

This commit refactors the variable names:
- jobName  jobIdentifier
- contactName  contactIdentifier

This change improves code clarity and reflects the actual role
of these variables, ensuring better understanding
and avoiding potential confusion in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Validation for Unmatching Contact and Job Associations
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there was no check to validate whether a contact and job
 were actually matched before attempting to unmatch them.
This could lead to incorrect behavior, such as trying to unmatch
a contact from a job they were never associated with,
or unmatching a contact who has no job at all.

This commit adds validation logic to:
- Ensure the contact has jobs associated before unmatching.
- Ensure the job has contacts associated before unmatching.
- Provide clear error messages if the contact
and job are not matched together or if either has no associations.

This change prevents illogical unmatching operations and
improves the overall stability and accuracy of the unmatching process.

Standardize JavaDoc comments by enforcing punctuation
at the end of all sentences and capitalizing the first
letter in descriptions, including in @param, @return, and
@throws sections. This change follows the newly agreed coding
standard for JavaDoc consistency across the project.
Apply changes on an ad-hoc basis, with a full review
planned near the end of the project for consistency.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor UnmatchCommand Logic and Improve Matching Validation
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor the validation logic in UnmatchCommand to ensure proper
bidirectional matching between contacts and jobs before unmatching.
- Replace redundant checks with a single condition to verify
if both the contact and job are symmetrically matched.
- Move the assert statement before the condition to catch
potential mismatched states early, as asymmetry
should not occur in the system.
- Update comments for clarity to better reflect the intent of the code.

This change improves the correctness of
unmatching operations and enhances readability.

- Modified UML diagram to replace DeleteCommand with
DeleteContactCommand for improved specificity.
- Updated sequence and participant names in the diagram
to reflect the change from a generic delete command
to one targeting contact deletion.
- Ensured consistency in naming across Logic and Model components.

This update clarifies the intent and functionality
of the DeleteContactCommand in the systems UML representation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update alekkwek18.md With Contributions Up To V1.4

commitResults.messageBody:
Screen job command currently displays the full list when no candidates
 match the job requirements. This can cause
 confusion for users expecting an empty list when no matches are found.

Update the command to display an empty list if no candidates match,
returning "0 candidates found" to improve clarity. Using
an empty list provides more accurate feedback and prevents
misunderstanding about available candidates.

commitResults.messageTitle: Exclude already matched contacts from screen job results
commitResults.messageBody:
Modify ScreenJobCommand to exclude contacts that have
already been matched with any job from the screen job results.
This change refines the filter criteria by adding a check using
Persons isMatchPresent() method, ensuring that
only unmatched contacts are displayed as eligible candidates.

This resolves issue #129 and improves result
accuracy for the screen job command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor UnmatchCommand to remove bidirectional association
commitResults.messageBody:
The UnmatchCommand currently maintains a bidirectional association
between Job and Contact, which increases complexity and requires
additional maintenance to ensure both sides are synchronized.

To streamline the association, this commit removes the
job-to-contact reference, simplifying matching logic and relying
only on Contact to store job associations.

Changes made:
- Refactor `validateMatching` and `unmatchContactFromJob` methods
  to use only Contact for validation and modification.
- Update execute method in UnmatchCommand to reflect unidirectional
  association, eliminating redundant checks and reducing maintenance.

This change improves code maintainability by reducing the need for
symmetric updates and aligns with team feedback on bidirectional
association removal.

Additionally, this commit fixes issue #142 where the `screen job`
command was not correctly filtering matched contacts due to
redundant bidirectional references. The filtering logic now
accurately reflects the latest contact-job associations.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement ListAllCommand to list all entities at once
commitResults.messageBody:
Add a new `ListAllCommand` class to list all contacts, companies,
and jobs in the address book simultaneously.
This command uses existing predicates to update the filtered
lists for each entity, enhancing user experience by
consolidating individual list commands.

- Define `ENTITY_WORD` as "all"
- Update all filtered lists using `PREDICATE_SHOW_ALL_PERSONS`,
`PREDICATE_SHOW_ALL_COMPANIES`, and `PREDICATE_SHOW_ALL_JOBS`
- Return `CommandResult` with a combined success message

This feature provides a convenient way for users to view all
entities at once, improving accessibility and navigation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add logging and assertions to UnmatchCommand for improved diagnostics
commitResults.messageBody:
Enhance `UnmatchCommand` by adding logging to track
command execution and assertions to validate key assumptions:
- Initialize a logger to capture command execution flow,
with informative messages on contact and job indices,
matching validation, and unmatching status.
- Add assertions to ensure non-null indices and valid
retrieval of contact and job entities, improving code reliability.

These changes enhance traceability during command execution
and help catch potential issues early.

Add UnmatchCommandTest to verify unmatch functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces UnmatchCommandTest to thoroughly test the
functionality of UnmatchCommand. Key tests include:

- Successfully unmatching a contact and job that
 were previously matched.
- Handling cases where a contact has no matching job or
attempts to unmatch a job not associated with them.

The test ensures that UnmatchCommand correctly updates the model state,
removing job associations from contacts as expected, and verifies that
the expected feedback message is returned for each scenario.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enhance screen command to screen all candidates with case-insensitive matching
commitResults.messageBody:
- Update ScreenJobCommand to operate on the entire list of contacts,
ignoring any current filters, to ensure all candidates are screened.
- Add new methods `getFullPersonList` and `getFullJobList`
to Model interface and implement them in ModelManager to retrieve
 unfiltered lists of persons and jobs, allowing comprehensive screening.
- Modify `roleMatchesJobPredicate` to support case-insensitive
partial matching by converting both job names and person roles
to lowercase, allowing flexible matching.
- Refine usage message for `screen job` command to clarify
functionality and improve readability, making
parameters and examples more accessible.
